{
  "text": "Based on the above studies, we synthesized EGCGcapped GNPs (EGCG-GNPs) to facilitate the delivery of EGCG by engulfment of nanoparticles in a single step. Different from traditional methods, this green nanotechnology introduced no other chemicals. [CITATION_1] This method can be an optimal solution to clinical applications of EGCG, improving its poor bioavailability and decreasing its adverse effects. The inhibitory effects of free EGCG and EGCG-GNPs on LPS-induced OC formation in vitro and bone destruction in vivo were demonstrated and compared. The corresponding mechanisms were investigated afterward.",
